    <briefdescription>
<para>API to query the status of the Headset fit. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Shared Object:\n perception.magicleap</title><para></para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="warning"><para>THIS API IS DEPRECATED IN FAVOR OF OPENXR XR_ML_user_calibration EXTENSION: <ulink url="https://registry.khronos.org/OpenXR/specs/1.0/html/xrspec.html#XR_ML_user_calibration">https://registry.khronos.org/OpenXR/specs/1.0/html/xrspec.html#XR_ML_user_calibration</ulink></para>
</simplesect>
This API can be used to determine the fit of the headset on the user. The API will only look to see if the pupil location corresponding to the neutral gaze is centered on the image. What this means is that we can only look for a certain type of bad fits. However this covers majority of the bad fit cases. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
